item.title: United said it had this woman's missing bag. She tracked it to a residential address
item.description: When Valerie Szybala's bag never arrived with her United Airlines flight, the airline told her it had it safe and ready for delivery. But her Airtag said otherwise -- and she tracked it to a residential address in Virginia.

item.title: Teenage pilot makes emergency landing near two-lane highway in California
item.description: A teenage pilot flying a single-engine plane with several family members on board made an emergency landing near a two-lane highway in the San Bernardino National Forest in California on Monday.

item.title: Israel's far-right Ben Gvir visits flashpoint Jerusalem holy site as Palestinians slam 'provocation'
item.description: Israeli far right national security minister Itamar Ben Gvir visited the compound of Jerusalem's Al Aqsa mosque, known as Temple mount in Judaism, on Tuesday in a move that drew Palestinian condemnation and stood against Israeli warnings.

item.title: Tesla's shares plunge further on weaker than expected sales
item.description: Tesla shares plunged more about 13% in early trading Tuesday, as weaker than expected global sales caused the company's massive slide in its share price that began last year to continue.

item.title: Global markets struggle to put last year's misery behind them
item.description: European and Asian stocks pushed higher on the first major trading day of 2023 as investors try to look beyond a gloomy outlook for the world economy, China's worst Covid outbreak and stubbornly high inflation in Europe.

item.title: This tech company is clearing out recurring meetings from employee calendars
item.description: One tech company is trying to help its employees kick off the new year with a clean slate, or at least an emptier calendar.

item.title: The latest on the new Congress and House speaker vote
item.description: The newly elected 118th Congress will officially be sworn in on Jan. 3 and the House speaker election will be held. Follow here for the latest live news updates from Capitol Hill.

item.title: Russia's war in Ukraine
item.description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky said Russia is planning a prolonged campaign of attacks with Iranian-made Shahed drones to exhaust Ukraine. Follow for live news updates.

item.title: Florida Gov. DeSantis begins second term with spotlight on presidential ambitions
item.description: Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis swore an oath to a second term in office on Tuesday, trumpeting his accomplishments of the last four years that he said have made the state "a promised land of sanity," as he pledged to make Florida a beacon for freedom across the nation.

item.title: Missouri is scheduled to carry out first US execution of an openly transgender person today
item.description: Missouri on Tuesday is scheduled to execute Amber McLaughlin, a transgender woman convicted of a 2003 murder, who unsuccessfully sought clemency from the governor in part because the jury at her trial did not vote for a death sentence.

item.title: 'The View' pays tribute to Barbara Walters
item.description: "The View" returned from its holiday hiatus to pay tribute to its creator, Barbara Walters, who died last week at 93 years old.

item.title: Bills player Damar Hamlin is in critical condition after collapsing from a cardiac arrest on the field, team says
item.description: Buffalo Bills safety Damar Hamlin collapsed on the field Monday night after making a tackle in the first quarter of the Bills game against the Cincinnati Bengals.

item.title: Major storm leaves trail of destruction as it barrels across Central US with powerful tornadoes, flooding and heavy snow
item.description: A major multi-hazard storm barreling across the country continues to bring the risk of strong tornadoes and flooding to the South, and ice and snow to the Plains and Upper Midwest on Tuesday.

item.title: Buffalo Bills safety Damar Hamlin was cherishing every moment in the NFL before his collapse
item.description: The current NFL season had seen Buffalo Bills player Damar Hamlin establish him in the team before he suffered a cardiac arrest and collapsed during the Bills' game against the Cincinnati Bengals on Monday.

item.title: There wasn't a single bank robbery in Denmark last year
item.description: The number of bank robberies in Denmark fell to zero last year, as beefed-up security and reduced use of cash in the Nordic country make holdups less lucrative.

item.title: Al Roker set to return to 'Today' after hospitalizations
item.description: Al Roker's colleagues shared the good news Tuesday that the beloved weatherman will be back on the air soon.

item.title: McCarthy faces make-or-break moment in vote to elect House speaker
item.description: House GOP leader Kevin McCarthy faces a make-or-break moment on Tuesday, as he seeks to lock down the support necessary to become the next speaker in a vote that could turn into a chaotic and contentious once-in-a-century floor fight.

item.title: Has your boss recently given you a nice raise so you'll stay? Are you an employer paying workers more not to quit?
item.description: Workers who stick with the same employers are enjoying the biggest raises in nearly a quarter century.

item.title: NFL star Damar Hamlin in critical condition after cardiac arrest
item.description: Buffalo Bills player Damar Hamlin is in critical condition after suffering cardiac arrest when he collapsed on the field during a game against the Cincinnati Bengals, his team said. Follow live updates here.

item.title: Skip Bayless apologizes for tweet after Damar Hamlin's collapse
item.description: Fox Sports host Skip Bayless apologized for hosting his FS1 show "Undisputed" Tuesday morning following a controversial tweet about a football player who suffered a medical emergency during a game.

item.title: Montgomery, Alabama, airport worker died after being 'ingested' into aircraft engine, NTSB says
item.description: A worker who died in an accident at the Montgomery Regional Airport Saturday "was ingested into the engine" of an aircraft, according to a statement from the National Transportation Safety Board.

item.title: A Pennsylvania police chief was killed after he 'ran towards danger' pursuing a suspect
item.description: Justin McIntire, the police chief in Brackenridge, was shot in the head while chasing a man wanted by Pennsylvania State Police, officials said.

item.title: Jeremy Renner is in ICU recovering from 2 surgeries after being injured in snow plowing incident
item.description: "Hawkeye" actor Jeremy Renner is recovering from surgery after suffering "blunt chest trauma and orthopedic injuries" in a New Year's Day snow plowing accident in Nevada, a spokesperson for the actor said.

item.title: Influx of Cuban migrants shuts down national park in Florida
item.description: Dry Tortugas National Park in the Florida Keys is temporarily closed to the public due to an influx of migrants from Cuba.

item.title: Kate Bosworth wrote a letter to her younger self for her 40th birthday
item.description: Kate Bosworth shared a letter she wrote to her younger self for her 40th birthday.

item.title: France's César film awards ban nominees under investigation for sexual violence from ceremony
item.description: France's equivalent of the Oscars -- the Césars ​-- says it is banning anyone currently under investigation for acts of violence, "especially those of a sexual nature," from attending its awards ceremony next month "out of respect for any possible victims."

item.title: 'Surviving R.Kelly': Final installment examines trial and more details
item.description: "Surviving R. Kelly" raised awareness of the abuse allegations against the singer who is now serving time. On Monday night, the final installment of the docuseries began airing on Lifetime.

item.title: Funeral procession for Pelé begins after thousands, including Brazil's president Lula da Silva, visited 24-hour wake
item.description: A funeral procession which will take legendary footballer Pelé to his final resting place has begun Tuesday.

item.title: Brazilian authorities intend to revive fraud case against George Santos
item.description: Law enforcement officials in Brazil will reinstate fraud charges against Rep.-elect George Santos, the Rio de Janeiro prosecutor's office tells CNN, as the New York Republican officially assumes his role in the US House Tuesday under a cloud of suspicion over his dubious resume.

item.title: 'Yellowstone' Season 5 will return this summer
item.description: "Yellowstone" viewers will have to wait until summer to see the conclusion of Season 5.
